1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 SJR___ COMMENDING RETIRED U.S. ARMY COLONEL SHAWN THOMAS
5 PRICKETT.
6
7 WHEREAS, retired U.S. Army Colonel Shawn Thomas
8 Prickett has demonstrated extraordinary leadership and
9 selfless commitment to America's veterans through years of
10 volunteer service and advocacy; and
11 WHEREAS, Colonel Prickett serves as President of the
12 National Whitetail Warrior Project, an organization
13 dedicated to providing life-changing outdoor experiences for
14 disabled veterans through hunting, fellowship, and
15 connection in the great outdoors; and
16 WHEREAS, since becoming involved with the
17 organization in 2012 and assuming the role of President in
18 August 2016, Colonel Prickett has devoted countless hours to
19 expanding opportunities for veterans to reconnect, heal, and
20 build lasting bonds with fellow service members; and
21 WHEREAS, he has personally organized and led 230
22 separate veteran hunts, creating meaningful experiences that
23 bring together those who have served our nation and
24 providing moments of fellowship, reflection, and renewal;
25 and
26 WHEREAS, the National Whitetail Warrior Project,
27 under his leadership, has served more than 500 veterans,
28 partnered with 14 Alabama landowners, and coordinated hunts
Page 1

partnered with 14 Alabama landowners, and coordinated hunts
SJR86 Enrolled
29 across Pennsylvania, Texas, Missouri, New York, Mississippi,
30 Wyoming, South Dakota, Kansas, Tennessee, and Kentucky,
31 extending the spirit of service far beyond state lines; and
32 WHEREAS, Colonel Prickett has helped raise over
33 $500,000 in support of disabled veterans, ensuring that
34 these experiences are made available at no cost to those who
35 have sacrificed so much in defense of our nation; and
36 WHEREAS, his efforts reflect a deep belief that
37 gathering veterans together in the outdoors fosters healing,
38 strengthens bonds of brotherhood and sisterhood, and affirms
39 that the spirit of service continues long after the uniform
40 is hung up; and
41 WHEREAS, through his dedication, generosity of
42 spirit, and continued service to those who have served,
43 Colonel Prickett exemplifies the very highest ideals of
44 leadership, citizenship, and devotion to our nation's
45 veterans; now therefore,
46 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
47 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That the highest commendation and
48 deepest appreciation are hereby extended to retired U.S.
49 Army Colonel Shawn Thomas Prickett in recognition of his
50 extraordinary service to our nation's veterans, his
51 exceptional volunteer leadership, and his unwavering
52 commitment to honoring and supporting those who have served
53 through the National Whitetail Warrior Project.
54 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, That a copy of this
55 resolution be presented to Colonel Prickett as a lasting
56 token of the esteem, gratitude, and admiration of the
Page 2

token of the esteem, gratitude, and admiration of the
